long_desc.thetext:
I have noticed a strange behaviour of maximized window when user tries to resize the window. First of all, the behaviour is different for Firefox 2, Internet Explorer 6 and Opera 9.
In Firefox 2 the window can be resized from all sides. But control buttons (minimize, maximize and close) will disappear if user resizes (changes width of) the window from right side.
In IE 6 and Opera 9 the window can be only resized from left and top sides but not from right and bottom sides.
The resized window cannot be moved in all browsers. Moreover, mode property does not change its value and stays as "maximized".

Code snippet:
var wnd = new qx.ui.window.Window("Test");
wnd.set({
    border : new qx.ui.core.Border(1, "solid", "#000000"),
    left : 10,
    top : 10,
    width : 300,
    height : 200
});
wnd.addToDocument();
wnd.maximize();
wnd.show();
var onResize = function(oEvent) {
    this.debug(this.getMode());
}
wnd.addEventListener("changeWidth", onResize, wnd);
wnd.addEventListener("changeHeight", onResize, wnd);

Best regards,
Dioc
